, caste, and gender positions. Dalit women's narratives about their experiences with cancer present a powerful and poignant critique of the sociocultural and political-economic conditions that marginalize them and jeopardize their health and well-being in twenty-first-century India.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aDalit womenxCancerxTreatmentzIndiazTamil Naduy21st century. 0aDalit womenxHealth and hygienezIndiazTamil Naduy21st century. 0aDalit womenzIndiazTamil NaduxEconomic conditionsy21st century. 0aDalit womenzIndiazTamil NaduxSocial conditionsy21st century. 0aEqualityzIndiazTamil Naduy21st century. 0aPublic healthzIndiazTamil Naduy21st century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / Asian Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076649340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520386556?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520386556423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520386556/original  a978-3-11-076649-3  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY